description._content: (2008) Grammy Award-winning producer Quincy Jones presented a platinum copy of 'Fly Me to the Moon' to Senator John Glenn and Apollo 11 Commander Neil Armstrong during NASA's 50th anniversary gala in 2008, a song he originally produced and performed with Frank Sinatra. Senator Glenn became the first American to orbit the Earth as an astronaut in NASA's Mercury Program. Neil Armstrong is the first person to set foot on the moon. During the gala, Jones performed 'Fly Me to the Moon' with Frank Sinatra Jr. Image Credit: NASA/Bill Ingalls www.nasa.gov/topics/people/galleries/armstrong_2008.html
